cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a fog architecture for providing services to end users based on a cluster of static vehicles in a parking lot. The proposed architecture is connected to the central data center through an optical infrastructure. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a fog architecture that utilizes spare processing capabilities of vehicles to provide services to end users. This involves distributed computing and falls under the scope of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a mixed integer linear programming (MILP) model to optimize the power consumption of the overall architecture. This falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of software packages variety in vehicles on the assignment decision and the overall power consumption. This falls under the scope of computers and society. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss security, the proposed architecture involves communication between vehicles and the central data center, which may require security measures. This falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
